'''''Xanagrams''''' is an educational game that is a cross between a [[crossword puzzle]] and [[Scrabble]] released between 1983 and 1984 for the [[Acorn Electron]], [[Amstrad CPC]], [[BBC Micro]], [[Commodore 64]], [[Sharp MZ]] and [[ZX Spectrum]]. It was given away for free with the [[Amstrad CPC 464]] and was a popular game.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amstrad CPC 464|url=http://www.retrogamer.net/profiles/hardware/amstrad-cpc-464/|website=Retro Gamer|date=27 March 2014 |access-date=24 August 2016}}</ref> There are 3 difficulty level to the game, from middle school aged to adults. A game can consist of 1-5 words and the player is given a jumble of letters to sort out to form the correct words.{{cn|date=August 2016}}

